						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vīraṭṭāṉēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Rajadhiraja II(?) = c. 1163-1178 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 32 cows for a perpetual lamp for god Tiruvīraṭṭaṉam-uḍaiyār by Pālūr Vāṇarāyaṉ Vēmbaṉ Sōḻaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājādhirāja-nāḍuḍaiyān. The donor appears to have belonged to Uḍaikkāḍu-nāḍu on the northern bank of Peṇṇai, in Vāṇagappāḍi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Madirāntaka-vaḷanāḍu. The record is engraved in characters of about the 11th century.</p>						

						</summary>
